**section 1: setting up the project**

first, create a new svelte project using the command `svelte create my-anilist-app`. this will create a new directory called `my-anilist-app` with the basic file structure for a svelte app.

next, install the required dependencies for the app by running the command `npm install`. this will install svelte, material ui, and graphql.

***section 2: configuring the graphql query***

to retrieve anime titles and ratings from anilist, we'll need to create a graphql query. open the ` queries/index.js` file and add the following code:
```js
import { gql } from '@apollo/client';

export const get_anime_titles = gql`
  query getanimetitles {
    animetitles(limit: 100) {
      edges {
        node {
          id
          title
          rating
        }
      }
    }
  }
`;
```
this query retrieves the first 100 anime titles and their ratings from anilist.

***section 3: displaying the anime titles and ratings***

next, we'll create the material ui components to display the anime titles and ratings. open the `components/animelist.svelte` file and add the following code:
```html
<script>
  import { usequery } from '@apollo/client';

  const get_anime_titles = gql`
    query getanimetitles {
      animetitles(limit: 100) {
        edges {
          node {
            id
            title
            rating
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
</script>

<ul>
  {#each $animetitles as anime}
    <li>
      <h2>{anime.title}</h2>
      <p>{anime.rating}</p>
    </li>
  {/each}
</ul>
```
this component uses the `usequery` hook from apollo client to retrieve the anime titles and ratings from the graphql query we defined earlier. it then displays the titles and ratings in a list.

***section 4: connecting to anilist and displaying the data***

finally, we need to connect to anilist and display the data in our app. open the `main.js` file and add the following code:
```js
import { apolloclient, inmemorycache } from '@apollo/client';
import { get_anime_titles } from './queries/index';

const client = new apolloclient({
  uri: 'https://api.anilist.co/graphql',
  cache: new inmemorycache(),
});

const { data, error } = await client.query({
  query: get_anime_titles,
});

if (error) {
  console.error(error);
}

const animelist = data.animetitles.edges.map(edge => edge.node);

const app = new svelteapp({
  target: document.getelementbyid('app'),
  components: {
    animelist,
  },
  data: {
    animelist,
  },
});

app.mount();
```
this code sets up an apollo client instance with the anilist api endpoint, retrieves the anime titles and ratings using the graphql query, and displays the data in the `animelist` component.

